name: Animate Wall
text: Enchant Wall\nEnchanted Wall can attack as though it didn't have defender.
flavor: "When you have been bitten with fangs of granite, you start to long for the ivory sabers of tigers."\n—Norin the Wary

name: Archangel
text: Flying, vigilance
flavor: "My mother once told me angels sing their swords' names with each strike."\n—Sisay, Captain of the Weatherlight

name: Ardent Militia
text: Vigilance
flavor: Some fight for honor and some for gold, but the militia fight for hearth and home.

name: Armageddon
text: Destroy all lands.

name: Armored Pegasus
text: Flying
flavor: Asked how it survived a run-in with a bog imp, the pegasus just shook its mane and burped.

name: Castle
text: Untapped creatures you control get +0/+2.
flavor: "Hang out our banners on the outward walls; / The cry is still, ‘They come'; our castle's strength / Will laugh a siege to scorn."\n—William Shakespeare, Macbeth

name: Celestial Dawn
text: Lands you control are Plains.\nNonland cards you own that aren't on the battlefield, spells you control, and nonland permanents you control are white.\nYou may spend white mana as though it were mana of any color. You may spend other mana only as though it were colorless mana.

name: Circle of Protection: Black
text: {1}: The next time a black source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Circle of Protection: Blue
text: {1}: The next time a blue source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Circle of Protection: Green
text: {1}: The next time a green source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Circle of Protection: Red
text: {1}: The next time a red source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Circle of Protection: White
text: {1}: The next time a white source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Crusade
text: White creatures get +1/+1.

name: D'Avenant Archer
text: {T}: D'Avenant Archer deals 1 damage to target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: Avenant's archers are also trained as poets, so that each arrow is guided by a fragment of verse.

name: Daraja Griffin
text: Flying\nSacrifice Daraja Griffin: Destroy target black creature.
flavor: "And the flamingos said, ‘Get out of our nest—we can't be seen with the likes of you!' So, the griffin ate them."\n—Azeworai, "The Ugly Bird"

name: Disenchant
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.

name: Divine Transformation
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +3/+3.
flavor: Glory surged through her and radiance surrounded her. All things were possible with the blessing of the Divine.

name: Ekundu Griffin
text: Flying, first strike
flavor: "My goat was a small price to pay for the chance to see the hunting griffin dive and seize it."\n—Suq'Ata trader

name: Enlightened Tutor
text: Search your library for an artifact or enchantment card and reveal that card. Shuffle your library, then put the card on top of it.
flavor: "I do not teach. I simply reveal."\n—Daudi, Femeref tutor

name: Ethereal Champion
text: Pay 1 life: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to Ethereal Champion this turn.
flavor: "If I have learned anything as a wizard it is this: never fight your own battles."\n—Waffa, sorcerer of Nyomba

name: Exile
text: Exile target nonwhite attacking creature. You gain life equal to its toughness.

name: Healing Salve
text: Choose one —\n• Target player gains 3 life.\n• Prevent the next 3 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.

name: Heavy Ballista
text: {T}: Heavy Ballista deals 2 damage to target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: "Archers, ballistae—you can't even get near the island of Avenant."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Hero's Resolve
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+5.
flavor: "Destiny, chance, fate, fortune—they're all just ways of claiming your successes without claiming your failures."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Icatian Town
text: Put four 1/1 white Citizen creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Icatia's once-peaceful towns faced increasing attacks from orcs and goblins as the climate cooled. By the time the empire fell, they were little more than armed camps.

name: Infantry Veteran
text: {T}: Target attacking creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "The true dishonor for a soldier is surviving the war."\n—Telim'Tor

name: Kismet
text: Artifacts, creatures, and lands played by your opponents enter the battlefield tapped.
flavor: "Make people wait for what they want, and you have power over them. This is as true for merchants and militia as it is for cooks and couples."\n—Gwendlyn Di Corci

name: Kjeldoran Royal Guard
text: {T}: All combat damage that would be dealt to you by unblocked creatures this turn is dealt to Kjeldoran Royal Guard instead.
flavor: Honorable in battle, generous in death.\n—Motto of the Kjeldoran Royal Guard

name: Light of Day
text: Black creatures can't attack or block.
flavor: "I do not miss sunlight. The very memory of it burns my eyes."\n—Volrath

name: Longbow Archer
text: First strike; reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: "If it bears wings, I will pin it to the skies over Tefemburu."\n—Roya, Zhalfirin archer

name: Mesa Falcon
text: Flying\n{1}{W}: Mesa Falcon gets +0/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "The faith of Serra is borne on wings of hope."\n—Gulsen, abbey matron

name: Order of the Sacred Torch
text: {T}, Pay 1 life: Counter target black spell.
flavor: A blazing light to drive out the shadows.

name: Pacifism
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature can't attack or block.
flavor: For the first time in his life, Grakk felt a little warm and fuzzy inside.

name: Pearl Dragon
text: Flying\n{1}{W}: Pearl Dragon gets +0/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "They knew Bantau was lost when, to hide the pearl he had found on the beach, he swallowed it—and soon grew wings."\n—Hakim, Loreweaver

name: Regal Unicorn
flavor: Unicorns don't care if you believe in them any more than you care if they believe in you.

name: Remedy
text: Prevent the next 5 damage that would be dealt this turn to any number of target creatures and/or players, divided as you choose.
flavor: "These things will protect you while I'm gone, remind you of my love for you."\n—"Love Song of Night and Day"

name: Reprisal
text: Destroy target creature with power 4 or greater. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: "The meek shall fight as one, and they shall overcome even the greatest of foes."\n—Halvor Arenson, Kjeldoran priest

name: Resistance Fighter
text: Sacrifice Resistance Fighter: Prevent all combat damage target creature would deal this turn.
flavor: "My soldiers fought without hesitation, died without doubt."\n—Sidar Jabari

name: Reverse Damage
text: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage. You gain life equal to the damage prevented this way.

name: Samite Healer
text: {T}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.
flavor: Healers ultimately acquire the divine gifts of spiritual and physical wholeness. The most devout are also granted the ability to pass physical wholeness on to others.

name: Serenity
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, destroy all artifacts and enchantments. They can't be regenerated.
flavor: "Just think of me as the storm before the calm."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Serra's Blessing
text: Creatures you control have vigilance. (Attacking doesn't cause them to tap.)
flavor: "I have seen your strength imbued in angels' wings, and I have felt your sorrow rain down on the ruins brought by the Lord of the Wastes."\n—Hanna, Weatherlight navigator

name: Spirit Link
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nWhenever enchanted creature deals damage, you gain that much life.

name: Standing Troops
text: Vigilance
flavor: The less you have, the harder you fight for it.

name: Staunch Defenders
text: When Staunch Defenders enters the battlefield, you gain 4 life.
flavor: "Hold your position! Leave doubt for the dying!"\n—Tahngarth of the Weatherlight

name: Sunweb
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nFlying\nSunweb can't block creatures with power 2 or less.
flavor: "There is no sweeter music than the wails of a dying dragon."\n—Rashida Scalebane

name: Tariff
text: Each player sacrifices the creature he or she controls with the highest converted mana cost unless he or she pays that creature's mana cost. If two or more creatures a player controls are tied for highest cost, that player chooses one.

name: Tundra Wolves
text: First strike (This creature deals combat damage before creatures without first strike.)
flavor: I heard their eerie howling, the wolves calling their kindred across the frozen plains.

name: Unyaro Griffin
text: Flying\nSacrifice Unyaro Griffin: Counter target red instant or sorcery spell.
flavor: The griffin's shadow gives courage to the righteous and dread to the idle.

name: Venerable Monk
text: When Venerable Monk enters the battlefield, you gain 2 life.
flavor: His presence brings not only a strong arm but also renewed hope.

name: Wall of Swords
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nFlying
flavor: Sharper than wind, lighter than air.

name: Warmth
text: Whenever an opponent casts a red spell, you gain 2 life.
flavor: "Flame grows gentle with but a little distance."\n—Orim, Samite healer

name: Warrior's Honor
text: Creatures you control get +1/+1 until end of turn.

name: Wrath of God
text: Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated.

name: Abduction
text:
Enchant creature
When Abduction enters the battlefield, untap enchanted creature.
You control enchanted creature.
When enchanted creature dies, return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control.

name: Air Elemental
text: Flying
flavor: As insubstantial, and as powerful, as the wind that carries it.

name: Ancestral Memories
text: Look at the top seven cards of your library. Put two of them into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.

name: Boomerang
text: Return target permanent to its owner's hand.
flavor: A lie always returns; be careful how you catch it.

name: Browse
text: {2}{U}{U}: Look at the top five cards of your library, put one of them into your hand, and exile the rest.
flavor: "Once great literature—now great litter."\n—Jaya Ballard, task mage

name: Chill
text: Red spells cost {2} more to cast.
flavor: "Temper, temper."\n—Ertai, wizard adept

name: Counterspell
text: Counter target spell.

name: Daring Apprentice
text: {T}, Sacrifice Daring Apprentice: Counter target spell.
flavor: In front of every great wizard is a doomed apprentice.

name: Deflection
text: Change the target of target spell with a single target.
flavor:
Up and down,
over and through,
back around—
the joke's on you.

name: Desertion
text: Counter target spell. If an artifact or creature spell is countered this way, put that card onto the battlefield under your control instead of into its owner's graveyard.
flavor: First the insult, then the injury.

name: Diminishing Returns
text: Each player shuffles his or her hand and graveyard into his or her library. You exile the top ten cards of your library. Then each player draws up to seven cards.

name: Dream Cache
text: Draw three cards, then put two cards from your hand both on top of your library or both on the bottom of your library.
flavor: Dreams' riches are easily spent.\n—Suq'Ata adage

name: Flash
text: You may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield. If you do, sacrifice it unless you pay its mana cost reduced by up to {2}.

name: Flight
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has flying.

name: Fog Elemental
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhen Fog Elemental attacks or blocks, sacrifice it at end of combat.
flavor: "I've seen fog so thick you could cut it, but none that could cut me."\n—Tahngarth of the Weatherlight

name: Forget
text: Target player discards two cards, then draws as many cards as he or she discarded this way.

name: Gaseous Form
text: Enchant creature\nPrevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by enchanted creature.

name: Glacial Wall
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)
flavor: "Huge walls of ice block further travel. We can't believe they are natural."\n—Disa the Restless, journal entry

name: Harmattan Efreet
text: Flying\n{1}{U}{U}: Target creature gains flying until end of turn.
flavor: "One moment I was walking along the beach, and the next I was high in the air, staring into a hideous smiling face."\n—Tarub, Suq'Ata sailor

name: Horned Turtle
flavor: "So like men are they: a hardened shell with fragile flesh beneath."\n—Selenia, dark angel

name: Insight
text: Whenever an opponent casts a green spell, you draw a card.
flavor: "We can fight with you or against you. After my day, I'd prefer the former."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Inspiration
text: Target player draws two cards.
flavor: "Madness and genius are separated only by degrees of success."\n—Sidar Jabari

name: Juxtapose
text: You and target player exchange control of the creature you each control with the highest converted mana cost. Then exchange control of artifacts the same way. If two or more permanents a player controls are tied for highest cost, their controller chooses one of them.

name: Library of Lat-Nam
text: An opponent chooses one —\n• You draw three cards at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.\n• You search your library for a card, put that card into your hand, then shuffle your library.

name: Lord of Atlantis
text: Other Merfolk creatures get +1/+1 and have islandwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
flavor: A master of tactics, the lord of Atlantis makes his people bold in battle merely by arriving to lead them.

name: Mana Short
text: Tap all lands target player controls and empty his or her mana pool.

name: Memory Lapse
text: Counter target spell. If that spell is countered this way, put it on top of its owner's library instead of into that player's graveyard.
flavor: "Um . . . oh . . . what was I saying?"\n—Reveka, wizard savant

name: Merfolk of the Pearl Trident
flavor: Are merfolk humans with fins, or are humans merfolk with feet?

name: Mystical Tutor
text: Search your library for an instant or sorcery card and reveal that card. Shuffle your library, then put the card on top of it.
flavor: "To the tutors, a ‘poem of sand' was of little account, a ‘poem of ivory,' priceless."\n—Afari, Tales

name: Phantasmal Terrain
text: Enchant land\nAs Phantasmal Terrain enters the battlefield, choose a basic land type.\nEnchanted land is the chosen type.

name: Phantom Warrior
text: Phantom Warrior can't be blocked.
flavor: The phantom warrior comes from nowhere and returns there just as quickly.

name: Polymorph
text: Destroy target creature. It can't be regenerated. Its controller reveals cards from the top of his or her library until he or she reveals a creature card. The player puts that card onto the battlefield, then shuffles all other cards revealed this way into his or her library.
flavor: "Ahh! Opposable digits!"

name: Power Sink
text: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {X}. If he or she doesn't, that player taps all lands with mana abilities he or she controls and empties his or her mana pool.

name: Prodigal Sorcerer
text: {T}: Prodigal Sorcerer deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Occasionally members of the Institute of Arcane Study acquire a taste for worldly pleasures. Seldom do they have trouble finding employment.

name: Prosperity
text: Each player draws X cards.
flavor: "Wealth is a good thing, compared to poverty—your food is better, your robes are softer, and your companions have bathed more recently."\n—Kukemssa pirate

name: Psychic Transfer
text: If the difference between your life total and target player's life total is 5 or less, exchange life totals with that player.
flavor: "The memory of your existence will fade like the final stars of morning."\n—Kaervek

name: Psychic Venom
text: Enchant land\nWhenever enchanted land becomes tapped, Psychic Venom deals 2 damage to that land's controller.

name: Recall
text: Discard X cards, then return a card from your graveyard to your hand for each card discarded this way. Exile Recall.

name: Relearn
text: Return target instant or sorcery card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "Barrin taught me that the hardest lessons to grasp are the ones you've already learned."\n—Ertai, wizard adept

name: Remove Soul
text: Counter target creature spell.
flavor: Nethya stiffened suddenly, head cocked as if straining to hear some distant sound, then fell lifeless to the ground.

name: Sage Owl
text: Flying\nWhen Sage Owl enters the battlefield, look at the top four cards of your library, then put them back in any order.
flavor: The owl asks but never answers.

name: Sea Monster
text: Sea Monster can't attack unless defending player controls an Island.
flavor: Water is life. Or perhaps it is just something to wash it down with.

name: Segovian Leviathan
text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
flavor: "Leviathan, too! Can you catch him with a fish-hook or run a line round his tongue?"\n—The Bible, Job 41:1

name: Sibilant Spirit
text: Flying\nWhenever Sibilant Spirit attacks, defending player may draw a card.
flavor: She had expected death to roar, to thunder, to growl. She did not recognize it when it came hissing to her side.

name: Soldevi Sage
text: {T}, Sacrifice two lands: Draw three cards, then discard one of them.
flavor: "To hide the truth is more than folly—it is fatal."\n—Sorine Relicbane, Soldevi heretic

name: Spell Blast
text: Counter target spell with converted mana cost X. (For example, if that spell's mana cost is {3}{U}{U}, X is 5.)
flavor: Call it the thinking mage's version of brute force.

name: Storm Crow
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Storm crow descending, winter unending.\nStorm crow departing, summer is starting.

name: Tidal Surge
text: Tap up to three target creatures without flying.
flavor: "It is nature that gives us our boundaries and nature that enforces them."\n—Eladamri, Lord of Leaves

name: Unsummon
text: Return target creature to its owner's hand.

name: Vodalian Soldiers
flavor: "Vodalian rank is displayed by the colors and patterns of their skin. Beware the color red; that is the badge of the empress's favor."\n—Corbio, pearl diver

name: Wall of Air
text: Defender, flying (This creature can't attack, and it can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: When no falcons fly, beware the sky.\n—Femeref aphorism

name: Wind Drake
text: Flying
flavor: "No bird soars too high, if he soars with his own wings."\n—William Blake,\nThe Marriage of Heaven and Hell

name: Wind Spirit
text: Flying\nMenace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
flavor:
" . . . When the trees bow down their heads,
The wind is passing by."
—Christina Rossetti,
"Who Has Seen the Wind?"

name: Zur's Weirding
text: Players play with their hands revealed.\nIf a player would draw a card, he or she reveals it instead. Then any other player may pay 2 life. If a player does, put that card into its owner's graveyard. Otherwise, that player draws a card.

name: Abyssal Hunter
text: {B}, {T}: Tap target creature. Abyssal Hunter deals damage equal to Abyssal Hunter's power to that creature.
flavor: Some smiles show cheer; some merely show teeth.

name: Abyssal Specter
text: Flying\nWhenever Abyssal Specter deals damage to a player, that player discards a card.

name: Agonizing Memories
text: Look at target player's hand and choose two cards from it. Put them on top of that player's library in any order.
flavor: "An innocent man died because of my anger. That knowledge will haunt me for all eternity."\n—Karn, silver golem

name: Ashen Powder
text: Put target creature card from an opponent's graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.
flavor: "What you call decay, I call ripening. You'll gain no sustenance from this harvest."\n—Kaervek

name: Blight
text: Enchant land\nWhen enchanted land becomes tapped, destroy it.

name: Blighted Shaman
text: {T}, Sacrifice a Swamp: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.\n{T}, Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Blood Pet
text: Sacrifice Blood Pet: Add {B} to your mana pool.
flavor: "You are wrong," Volrath said. "I do not hate the living. They often prove quite useful to me." And then he laughed.

name: Bog Imp
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Don't be fooled by their looks. Think of them as little knives with wings.

name: Bog Rats
text: Bog Rats can't be blocked by Walls.
flavor: Their stench was vile and strong enough, but not nearly as powerful as their hunger.

name: Bog Wraith
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
flavor: It moved through the troops leaving no footprints, save on their souls.

name: Coercion
text: Target opponent reveals his or her hand. You choose a card from it. That player discards that card.
flavor: A rhino's bargain\n—Femeref expression meaning\n"a situation with no choices"

name: Derelor
text: Black spells you cast cost {B} more to cast.
flavor: "Strength it has, but at the cost of a continuous supply of energy. Such failure can bear only one result."\n—Execution order of Endrek Sahr,\nmaster breeder

name: Doomsday
text: Search your library and graveyard for five cards and exile the rest. Put the chosen cards on top of your library in any order. You lose half your life, rounded up.

name: Dread of Night
text: White creatures get -1/-1.
flavor: "These moonless, foreign skies keep me in thrall. Dark whispers echo in the night, and I cannot resist."\n—Selenia, dark angel

name: Drudge Skeletons
text: {B}: Regenerate Drudge Skeletons. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)
flavor: "The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, they never surrender, and they don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."\n—Nevinyrral, Necromancer's Handbook

name: Dry Spell
text: Dry Spell deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: "Wherever water is lacking, all things suffer."\n—Autumn Willow

name: Enfeeblement
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature gets -2/-2.
flavor: "If it is weak, either kill it or ignore it. Anything else honors it."\n—Kaervek

name: Evil Eye of Orms-by-Gore
text: Non-Eye creatures you control can't attack.\nEvil Eye of Orms-by-Gore can't be blocked except by Walls.
flavor: The highway of fear is the shortest route to defeat.

name: Fallen Angel
text: Flying\nSacrifice a creature: Fallen Angel gets +2/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "Angels are simply extensions of truth upon the fabric of life—and there is far more dark than light." —Baron Sengir

name: Fatal Blow
text: Destroy target creature that was dealt damage this turn. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: "What is crueler? To let a wound of the heart fester, or to simply cut it out?"\n—Crovax

name: Fear
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature has fear. (It can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)

name: Feast of the Unicorn
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +4/+0.
flavor: "Could there be a fouler act? No doubt the baron knows of one."\n—Autumn Willow

name: Feral Shadow
text: Flying
flavor: Not all shadows are cast by light—some are cast by darkness.

name: Forbidden Crypt
text: If you would draw a card, return a card from your graveyard to your hand instead. If you can't, you lose the game.\nIf a card would be put into your graveyard from anywhere, exile that card instead.

name: Gravebane Zombie
text: If Gravebane Zombie would die, put Gravebane Zombie on top of its owner's library instead.

name: Gravedigger
text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: A full coffin is like a full coffer—both are attractive to thieves.

name: Greed
text: {B}, Pay 2 life: Draw a card.
flavor: "There is no calamity greater than lavish desires. There is no greater guilt than discontentment. And there is no greater disaster than greed."\n—Lao Tsu, Tao Te Ching, (trans. Chan)

name: Hecatomb
text: When Hecatomb enters the battlefield, sacrifice Hecatomb unless you sacrifice four creatures.\nTap an untapped Swamp you control: Hecatomb deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Hidden Horror
text: When Hidden Horror enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you discard a creature card.

name: Howl from Beyond
text: Target creature gets +X/+0 until end of turn.

name: Infernal Contract
text: Draw four cards. You lose half your life, rounded up.
flavor: "But I signed nothing!"\n—Taraneh, Suq'Ata mage

name: Kjeldoran Dead
text: When Kjeldoran Dead enters the battlefield, sacrifice a creature.\n{B}: Regenerate Kjeldoran Dead.
flavor: "They shall drink sorrow's dregs. They shall kill those whom once they loved."\n—Lim-Dûl, the Necromancer

name: Leshrac's Rite
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has swampwalk. (It can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
flavor: "Bind me to thee, my soul to thine. I am your servant and your slave. Blood for blood, flesh for flesh, Leshrac, my lord."\n—Lim-Dûl, the Necromancer

name: Lost Soul
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
flavor: Her hand gently beckons, she whispers your name—but those who go with her are never the same.

name: Mind Warp
text: Look at target player's hand and choose X cards from it. That player discards those cards.
flavor: The hardest of wizards can have the softest of minds.

name: Mischievous Poltergeist
text: Flying\nPay 1 life: Regenerate Mischievous Poltergeist.
flavor: "The past is a ghost that haunts you from the moment it exists until the moment you don't."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Necrosavant
text: {3}{B}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Return Necrosavant from your graveyard to the battlefield. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.

name: Nightmare
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nNightmare's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Swamps you control.
flavor: As the poisoned land spreads, so does the nightmare's rage and terrifying strength.

name: Painful Memories
text: Look at target opponent's hand and choose a card from it. Put that card on top of that player's library.
flavor: "It is terrible how one brief action can live forever in memory."\n—Jolrael

name: Perish
text: Destroy all green creatures. They can't be regenerated.
flavor: "There will come a time when the voices of soil and seedling will sing only laments."\n—Oracle en-Vec

name: Pestilence
text: At the beginning of the end step, if no creatures are on the battlefield, sacrifice Pestilence.\n{B}: Pestilence deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.

name: Python
flavor: "How can you claim the gods are merciless when they robbed the snake of its limbs to give the other creatures a sporting chance?"\n—Hakim, Loreweaver

name: Rag Man
text: {B}{B}{B}, {T}: Target opponent reveals his or her hand and discards a creature card at random. Activate this ability only during your turn.
flavor: "Aw, he's just a silly, dirty little man. What's to be afraid of?"

name: Raise Dead
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: The earth cannot hold that which magic commands.

name: Razortooth Rats
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
flavor: "Men and rats both hunger: we for our playthings; they, for us."\n—Crovax

name: Scathe Zombies
flavor:
"They groaned, they stirred, they all uprose,
Nor spake, nor moved their eyes;
It had been strange, even in a dream,
To have seen those dead men rise."
—Samuel Coleridge,
"The Rime of the Ancient Mariner"

name: Sengir Autocrat
text: When Sengir Autocrat enters the battlefield, put three 0/1 black Serf creature tokens onto the battlefield.\nWhen Sengir Autocrat leaves the battlefield, exile all Serf tokens.

name: Strands of Night
text: {B}{B}, Pay 2 life, Sacrifice a Swamp: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: "I have seen the night torn into thin darkling strips and woven into shapes too bleak for dreams."\n—Crovax

name: Stromgald Cabal
text: {T}, Pay 1 life: Counter target white spell.
flavor: When the alliance between Balduvia and Kjeldor deprived Stromgald of easy victories, its agents were forced to fuel their rituals with their own flesh.

name: Stupor
text: Target opponent discards a card at random, then discards a card.
flavor: There are medicines for all afflictions but idleness.\n—Suq'Ata saying

name: Syphon Soul
text: Syphon Soul deals 2 damage to each other player. You gain life equal to the damage dealt this way.

name: Terror
text: Destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Vampiric Tutor
text: Search your library for a card, then shuffle your library and put that card on top of it. You lose 2 life.
flavor: "I write upon clean white parchment with a sharp quill and the blood of my students, divining their secrets."\n—Shauku, Endbringer

name: Zombie Master
text: Other Zombie creatures have swampwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)\nOther Zombies have "{B}: Regenerate this permanent."
flavor: He controlled the zombies even before his own death; now nothing can make them betray him.

name: Æther Flash
text: Whenever a creature enters the battlefield, Æther Flash deals 2 damage to it.
flavor: "You can't get there from here. Well, you can—it just won't be fun."\n—Ertai, wizard adept

name: Anaba Bodyguard
text: First strike (This creature deals combat damage before creatures without first strike.)
flavor: "Not all minotaurs are tribal. Some are freelance."\n—Eron the Relentless

name: Anaba Shaman
text: {R}, {T}: Anaba Shaman deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "The shamans? Ha! They are craven cows not capable of true magic."\n—Irini Sengir

name: Balduvian Barbarians
flavor: "Barbarian raids were a concern to those living in the northwest provinces, but the skyknights never dealt with the problem in a systematic way. They thought of the Balduvians as an ‘amusing model' of their forebears' culture."\n—Kjeldor: Ice Civilization

name: Balduvian Horde
text: When Balduvian Horde enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you discard a card at random.

name: Blaze
text: Blaze deals X damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Fire never dies alone.

name: Boil
text: Destroy all Islands.
flavor: "The fishers will throw out their nets and draw them back filled with dust."\n—Oracle en-Vec

name: Burrowing
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has mountainwalk. (It can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)

name: Conquer
text: Enchant land\nYou control enchanted land.
flavor: "Why do we trade with those despicable elves? You don't live in forests, you burn them!"\n—Avram Garrisson,\nLeader of the Knights of Stromgald

name: Crimson Hellkite
text: Flying\n{X}, {T}: Crimson Hellkite deals X damage to target creature. Spend only red mana on X.
flavor: "Dragonfire forged me a warrior."\n—Rashida Scalebane

name: Earthquake
text: Earthquake deals X damage to each creature without flying and each player.

name: Fervor
text: Creatures you control have haste. (They can attack and {T} as soon as they come under your control.)
flavor: "If your blood doesn't run hot, I will make it run in the sands!"\n—Maraxus of Keld

name: Final Fortune
text: Take an extra turn after this one. At the beginning of that turn's end step, you lose the game.
flavor: Want all, lose all.\n—Zhalfirin aphorism

name: Fire Elemental
flavor: Fire elementals are ruthless infernos, annihilating and consuming their foes in a frenzied holocaust. Crackling and blazing, they sear swift, terrible paths, leaving the land charred and scorched in their wake.

name: Firebreathing
text: Enchant creature\n{R}: Enchanted creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "Magic's only part of it, my friend. Diet does the rest."\n—Suq'Ata trader

name: Fit of Rage
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 and gains first strike until end of turn.
flavor: "Anger is fleeting; remorse is eternal."\n—Karn, silver golem

name: Flame Spirit
text: {R}: Flame Spirit gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "The spirit of the flame is the spirit of change."\n—Lovisa Coldeyes,\nBalduvian chieftain

name: Flashfires
text: Destroy all Plains.

name: Giant Strength
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2.
flavor: "O! it is excellent / To have a giant's strength, but it is tyrannous / To use it like a giant."\n—William Shakespeare,\nMeasure for Measure

name: Goblin Digging Team
text: {T}, Sacrifice Goblin Digging Team: Destroy target Wall.
flavor: "From down here we can make the whole wall collapse!"\n"Uh, yeah, boss, but how do we get out?"

name: Goblin Elite Infantry
text: Whenever Goblin Elite Infantry blocks or becomes blocked, it gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: They talk a good fight.

name: Goblin Hero
flavor: "When you're a goblin, you don't have to step forward to be a hero—everyone else just has to step back!"\n—Biggum Flodrot, goblin veteran

name: Goblin King
text: Other Goblin creatures get +1/+1 and have mountainwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)
flavor: To be king, Numsgil did in Blog, who did in Unkful, who did in Viddle, who did in Loll, who did in Alrok . . . ."

name: Goblin Recruiter
text: When Goblin Recruiter enters the battlefield, search your library for any number of Goblin cards and reveal those cards. Shuffle your library, then put them on top of it in any order.
flavor: "Next!"

name: Goblin Warrens
text: {2}{R}, Sacrifice two Goblins: Put three 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: "Goblins bred underground, their numbers hidden from the enemy until it was too late." —Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

name: Hammer of Bogardan
text: Hammer of Bogardan deals 3 damage to target creature or player.\n{2}{R}{R}{R}: Return Hammer of Bogardan from your graveyard to your hand. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.

name: Hulking Cyclops
text: Hulking Cyclops can't block.
flavor: Anyone can get around a cyclops, but few can stand in its way.

name: Illicit Auction
text: Each player may bid life for control of target creature. You start the bidding with a bid of 0. In turn order, each player may top the high bid. The bidding ends if the high bid stands. The high bidder loses life equal to the high bid and gains control of the creature. (This effect lasts indefinitely.)

name: Inferno
text: Inferno deals 6 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: "Some have said there is no subtlety to destruction. You know what? They're dead." —Jaya Ballard, task mage

name: Jokulhaups
text: Destroy all artifacts, creatures, and lands. They can't be regenerated.
flavor: "The raging waters had swept away trees, bridges, and even houses. My healers had much work to do."\n—Halvor Arenson, Kjeldoran priest

name: Lightning Blast
text: Lightning Blast deals 4 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "Those who fear the darkness have never seen what the light can do."\n—Selenia, dark angel

name: Manabarbs
text: Whenever a player taps a land for mana, Manabarbs deals 1 damage to that player.

name: Mountain Goat
text: Mountainwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)
flavor: Only the heroic and the mad follow mountain goat trails.

name: Orcish Artillery
text: {T}: Orcish Artillery deals 2 damage to target creature or player and 3 damage to you.
flavor: In a rare display of ingenuity, the orcs invented an incredibly destructive weapon. Most orcish artillerists are those who dared criticize its effectiveness.

name: Orcish Oriflamme
text: Attacking creatures you control get +1/+0.

name: Pillage
text: Destroy target artifact or land. It can't be regenerated.

name: Pyrotechnics
text: Pyrotechnics deals 4 damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures and/or players.
flavor: "Hi!ni!ya! Behold the man of flint, that's me! / Four lightnings zigzag from me, strike and return."\n—Navajo war chant

name: Raging Goblin
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: He raged at the world, at his family, at his life. But mostly he just raged.

name: Reckless Embermage
text: {1}{R}: Reckless Embermage deals 1 damage to target creature or player and 1 damage to itself.
flavor: Many mages have been consumed by their work.

name: Relentless Assault
text: Untap all creatures that attacked this turn. After this main phase, there is an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase.
flavor: "Flog and Squee / Up the tree / See the army / Flee, flee, flee."\n—Goblin nursery rhyme/war cry

name: Sabretooth Tiger
text: First strike
flavor: "I fear anything with teeth measured in handspans!"\n—Norin the Wary

name: Shatter
text: Destroy target artifact.

name: Shatterstorm
text: Destroy all artifacts. They can't be regenerated.
flavor: Chains of leaping fire and sizzling lightning laid waste the artificers' handiwork, sparing not a single device.

name: Shock
text: Shock deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Lightning tethers souls to the world.\n—Kor saying

name: Spitting Drake
text: Flying\n{R}: Spitting Drake gets +1/+0 until end of turn. Activate this ability only once each turn.
flavor: It prefers its meals cooked.

name: Spitting Earth
text: Spitting Earth deals damage to target creature equal to the number of Mountains you control.
flavor: "There are times solid ground gives precious little comfort."\n—Talibah, embermage

name: Stone Rain
text: Destroy target land.

name: Talruum Minotaur
text: Haste
flavor: Don't insult a Talruum unless your mount is swift.\n—Suq'Ata saying

name: Tremor
text: Tremor deals 1 damage to each creature without flying.
flavor: "Where do you run when the earth becomes your enemy?"\n—Naimag, Femeref philosopher

name: Vertigo
text: Vertigo deals 2 damage to target creature with flying. That creature loses flying until end of turn.
flavor: "I saw the wizard gesturing, but I didn't guess his plan until my aesthir cried out and went into a dive."\n—Arna Kennerüd, skyknight

name: Viashino Warrior
flavor: "When traveling the Great Desert avoid wearing the scales of lizards, for the Viashino rule the sands and look poorly on the skinning of their cousins."\n—Zhalfirin Guide to the Desert

name: Volcanic Dragon
text: Flying\nHaste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: Speed and fire are always a deadly combination.

name: Volcanic Geyser
text: Volcanic Geyser deals X damage to target creature or player.
flavor: My thunder comes before the lightning; my lightning comes before the clouds; my rain dries all the land it touches. What am I?\n—Femeref riddle

name: Wall of Fire
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{R}: Wall of Fire gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "Struggle, and you will only fan the flames."\n—Talibah, embermage

name: Birds of Paradise
text: Flying\n{T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.

name: Call of the Wild
text: {2}{G}{G}: Reveal the top card of your library. If it's a creature card, put it onto the battlefield. Otherwise, put it into your graveyard.
flavor: Thinking of dinner made Squee realize that the forest was probably thinking the same thing.

name: Cat Warriors
text: Forestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: These stealthy felines have survived so many battles that some believe they must possess many lives.

name: Creeping Mold
text: Destroy target artifact, enchantment, or land.
flavor: "Mold could catch you."\n—Suq'Ata insult

name: Dense Foliage
text: Creatures can't be the targets of spells.
flavor: "Big plants not only good for hidin', but full o' tasty bugs, too."\n—Squee, goblin cabin hand

name: Early Harvest
text: Target player untaps all basic lands he or she controls.
flavor: "Tonight we'll eat a farewell feast. Cold corn porridge is not enough. / Let's peel papayas, pineapples, and mangoes, drink coconut milk, / and bake bananas."\n—"Love Song of Night and Day"

name: Elder Druid
text: {3}{G}, {T}: You may tap or untap target artifact, creature, or land.
flavor: "Did clouds dance in his eyes,\ndid thorns play at his fingertips?"\n—Shesul Fass, faerie bard

name: Elven Cache
text: Return target card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Elves know where to harvest the best of the forest, for they planted it there themselves.

name: Elven Riders
text: Elven Riders can't be blocked except by Walls and/or creatures with flying.
flavor: Sometimes it is better to be swift of foot than strong of swordarm.\n—Elven proverb

name: Elvish Archers
text: First strike
flavor: "I tell you, there was so many arrows flying about you couldn't hardly see the sun. So I says to young Angus, ‘Well, at least now we're fighting in the shade!'"

name: Fallow Earth
text: Put target land on top of its owner's library.
flavor: ". . . and when the farmer awoke the next morning, all the seeds from his field were once again in their sacks."\n—Afari, Tales

name: Familiar Ground
text: Each creature you control can't be blocked by more than one creature.
flavor: "I'd rather fight on foreign soil. That way, if I lose I can blame it on the terrain."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Femeref Archers
text: {T}: Femeref Archers deals 4 damage to target attacking creature with flying.
flavor: "They say a Zhalfirin archer can split the eye of a griffin. Nonsense, of course; they have no faith to guide their darts."\n—Nuru, Femeref archer

name: Fog
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.

name: Fyndhorn Brownie
text: {2}{G}, {T}: Untap target creature.
flavor: "I've been insulted by drunks in a hundred inns, but never as skillfully or annoyingly as by those blasted brownies."\n—General Jarkeld, the Arctic Fox

name: Fyndhorn Elder
text: {T}: Add {G}{G} to your mana pool.
flavor: "Do we know what we're doing? Yes—the will of Freyalise."\n—Laina of the Elvish Council

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Giant Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: It's not far into the trap, as the crow flies.

name: Gorilla Chieftain
text: {1}{G}: Regenerate Gorilla Chieftain.
flavor: "In the soil of leadership sprout the seeds of immortality."\n—Kaysa, Elder Druid of the Juniper

name: Grizzly Bears
flavor: Don't try to outrun one of Dominaria's grizzlies; it'll catch you, knock you down, and eat you. Of course, you could run up a tree. In that case you'll get a nice view before it knocks the tree down and eats you.

name: Hurricane
text: Hurricane deals X damage to each creature with flying and each player.

name: Living Lands
text: All Forests are 1/1 creatures that are still lands.

name: Llanowar Elves
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: One bone broken for every twig snapped underfoot.\n—Llanowar penalty for trespassing

name: Lure
text: Enchant creature\nAll creatures able to block enchanted creature do so.
flavor: When setting a snare, success depends not on the quality of the trap, but the quality of the bait.

name: Maro
text: Maro's power and toughness are each equal to the number of cards in your hand.
flavor: No two see the same Maro.

name: Nature's Resurgence
text: Each player draws a card for each creature card in his or her graveyard.
flavor: Spring follows winter\n—Elvish expression meaning\n"all things pass"

name: Panther Warriors
flavor: The dogs of war are nothing compared to the cats.

name: Pradesh Gypsies
text: {1}{G}, {T}: Target creature gets -2/-0 until end of turn.
flavor: "A mysterious people indeed. Their origins are as secret as their traditions."\n—Lord Magnus of Llanowar

name: Radjan Spirit
text: {T}: Target creature loses flying until end of turn.

name: Rampant Growth
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Rath forces plants from its surface as one presses whey from cheese.

name: Redwood Treefolk
flavor: The soldiers chopped and chopped, and still the great tree stood, frowning down at them.

name: Regeneration
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\n{G}: Regenerate enchanted creature. (The next time that creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)

name: River Boa
text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)\n{G}: Regenerate River Boa.
flavor: "But no one heard the snake's gentle hiss for peace over the elephant's trumpeting of war."\n—Afari, Tales

name: Rowen
text: Reveal the first card you draw each turn. Whenever you reveal a basic land card this way, draw a card.
flavor: "I've dreamt of a second harvest but fear I will not see it."\n—Asmira, holy avenger

name: Scaled Wurm
flavor: "Flourishing during the Ice Age, these wurms were the bane of all Kjeldorans. Their great size and ferocity made them the subject of countless nightmares—they embodied the worst of the Ice Age."\n—Kjeldor: Ice Civilization

name: Shanodin Dryads
text: Forestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: Moving without sound, swift figures pass through branches and undergrowth completely unhindered. One with the trees around them, the dryads of Shanodin Forest are seen only when they wish to be.

name: Stalking Tiger
text: Stalking Tiger can't be blocked by more than one creature.
flavor: In the Jamuraan jungles, there is often no separating beauty from danger.

name: Stream of Life
text: Target player gains X life.

name: Summer Bloom
text: You may play up to three additional lands this turn.
flavor: Summer sends its kiss with warmth and blooming life.

name: Thicket Basilisk
text: Whenever Thicket Basilisk blocks or becomes blocked by a non-Wall creature, destroy that creature at end of combat.
flavor: Moss-covered statues littered the area, a macabre monument to the basilisk's terrible power.

name: Trained Armodon
flavor: These are its last days. Better to grow broad and heavy. Better that the enemy is crushed beneath its carcass.

name: Tranquil Grove
text: {1}{G}{G}: Destroy all other enchantments.

name: Tranquility
text: Destroy all enchantments.

name: Uktabi Orangutan
text: When Uktabi Orangutan enters the battlefield, destroy target artifact.
flavor: "Is it true that the apes wear furs of gold when they marry?"\n—Rana, Suq'Ata market fool

name: Uktabi Wildcats
text: Uktabi Wildcats's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Forests you control.\n{G}, Sacrifice a Forest: Regenerate Uktabi Wildcats.

name: Unseen Walker
text: Forestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)\n{1}{G}{G}: Target creature gains forestwalk until end of turn.
flavor: "To pass through the jungle: silence, courtesy, ferocity, as the occasion demands."\n—Kamau, "Proper Passage"

name: Untamed Wilds
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Verduran Enchantress
text: Whenever you cast an enchantment spell, you may draw a card.
flavor: Some say magic was first practiced by women, who have always felt strong ties to the land.

name: Vitalize
text: Untap all creatures you control.
flavor: "After waking to the magic of Llanowar, no dreams can compare."\n—Mirri of the Weatherlight

name: Waiting in the Weeds
text: Each player puts a 1/1 green Cat creature token onto the battlefield for each untapped Forest he or she controls.
flavor: The trees have ears, eyes, and teeth.

name: Warthog
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
flavor: "Too much work—it takes a long time to break them in, and more than a few recruits."\n—Grebog, goblin swine-rider

name: Wild Growth
text: Enchant land\nWhenever enchanted land is tapped for mana, its controller adds {G} to his or her mana pool (in addition to the mana the land produces).

name: Worldly Tutor
text: Search your library for a creature card and reveal that card. Shuffle your library, then put the card on top of it.
flavor: "Aselbo soon had the rhino eating from his palm and the snake waiting at his heels."\n—Afari, Tales

name: Wyluli Wolf
text: {T}: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "When one wolf calls, others follow. Who wants to fight creatures that eat scorpions?"\n—Maimun al-Wyluli, diary

name: Aladdin's Ring
text: {8}, {T}: Aladdin's Ring deals 4 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: ". . . The magician drew a ring off his finger . . . , saying: 'It is a talisman against all evil, so long as you obey me.'"\n—The Arabian Nights,\nJunior Classics trans.

name: Amber Prison
text: You may choose not to untap Amber Prison during your untap step.\n{4}, {T}: Tap target artifact, creature, or land. That permanent doesn't untap during its controller's untap step for as long as Amber Prison remains tapped.

name: Ankh of Mishra
text: Whenever a land enters the battlefield, Ankh of Mishra deals 2 damage to that land's controller.
flavor: Tawnos finally cracked the puzzle: the strange structures did not house Mishra's malevolent creations but were themselves among his creations.

name: Ashnod's Altar
text: Sacrifice a creature: Add {C}{C} to your mana pool.
flavor: The Brothers' War scarred the land, but Ashnod left her mark in the bloodlines of those she tortured.

name: Bottle of Suleiman
text: {1}, Sacrifice Bottle of Suleiman: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, put a 5/5 colorless Djinn artifact creature token with flying onto the battlefield. If you lose the flip, Bottle of Suleiman deals 5 damage to you.

name: Charcoal Diamond
text: Charcoal Diamond enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {B} to your mana pool.

name: Crystal Rod
text: Whenever a player casts a blue spell, you may pay {1}. If you do, you gain 1 life.

name: Cursed Totem
text: Activated abilities of creatures can't be activated.
flavor: Pass me from soul to soul, / soldier to herder, herder to beast, beast to soil / until I am everywhere. / Then pass me those souls.\n—Totem inscription (translated)

name: Dancing Scimitar
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Bobbing merrily from opponent to opponent, the scimitar began adding playful little flourishes to its strokes; it even turned a couple of somersaults.

name: Dingus Egg
text: Whenever a land is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, Dingus Egg deals 2 damage to that land's controller.

name: Disrupting Scepter
text: {3}, {T}: Target player discards a card. Activate this ability only during your turn.

name: Dragon Engine
text: {2}: Dragon Engine gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "How is it the legged engines seem so much more alive than their wheeled counterparts? Simply, they were born, not made."\n—Mishra

name: Dragon Mask
text: {3}, {T}: Target creature you control gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Return it to its owner's hand at the beginning of the next end step. (Return it only if it's on the battlefield.)
flavor: "With no further options, I was forced to don the mask."\n—Rashida Scalebane

name: Fire Diamond
text: Fire Diamond enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {R} to your mana pool.

name: Flying Carpet
text: {2}, {T}: Target creature gains flying until end of turn.

name: Fountain of Youth
text: {2}, {T}: You gain 1 life.
flavor: The fountain had stood in the town square for centuries, but only the pigeons knew its secret.

name: Glasses of Urza
text: {T}: Look at target player's hand.

name: Grinning Totem
text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice Grinning Totem: Search target opponent's library for a card and exile it. Then that player shuffles his or her library. Until the beginning of your next upkeep, you may play that card. At the beginning of your next upkeep, if you haven't played it, put it into its owner's graveyard.

name: Howling Mine
text: At the beginning of each player's draw step, if Howling Mine is untapped, that player draws an additional card.

name: Iron Star
text: Whenever a player casts a red spell, you may pay {1}. If you do, you gain 1 life.

name: Ivory Cup
text: Whenever a player casts a white spell, you may pay {1}. If you do, you gain 1 life.

name: Jade Monolith
text: {1}: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to target creature this turn, that source deals that damage to you instead.

name: Jalum Tome
text: {2}, {T}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
flavor: This timeworn relic was responsible for many of Urza's victories, though he never fully comprehended its mystic runes.

name: Jayemdae Tome
text: {4}, {T}: Draw a card.

name: Lead Golem
text: Whenever Lead Golem attacks, it doesn't untap during its controller's next untap step.
flavor: Slow and heavy swings the club.

name: Mana Prism
text: {T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.\n{1}, {T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.

name: Marble Diamond
text: Marble Diamond enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {W} to your mana pool.

name: Meekstone
text: Creatures with power 3 or greater don't untap during their controllers' untap steps.
flavor: When the mighty sleep, the lowly prowl.

name: Millstone
text: {2}, {T}: Target player puts the top two cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard.
flavor: More than one mage has been driven insane by the sound of the millstone relentlessly grinding away.

name: Moss Diamond
text: Moss Diamond enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.

name: Mystic Compass
text: {1}, {T}: Target land becomes the basic land type of your choice until end of turn.

name: Obsianus Golem
flavor: "The foot stone is connected to the ankle stone, the ankle stone is connected to the leg stone . . . ."\n—"Song of the Artificer"

name: Ornithopter
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: "It has been my honor to improve on the Thran's original design. Perhaps history will remember me in some small part for my work."\n—Urza, in his apprenticeship

name: Patagia Golem
text: {3}: Patagia Golem gains flying until end of turn.
flavor: It scattered falcons like a lion hunting among jackals.

name: Pentagram of the Ages
text: {4}, {T}: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.
flavor: A mirror, a shield, a promise, a great distance, and a kind word—five ways to avoid harm.

name: Phyrexian Vault
text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature: Draw a card.
flavor: "The secrets of Phyrexia are expensive. You will pay in brass and bone, steel and sinew."\n—Kaervek

name: Primal Clay
text: As Primal Clay enters the battlefield, it becomes your choice of a 3/3 artifact creature, a 2/2 artifact creature with flying, or a 1/6 Wall artifact creature with defender in addition to its other types. (A creature with defender can't attack.)

name: Rod of Ruin
